'''布萊恩·約瑟夫·切斯基'''（{{lang-en|Brian Joseph Chesky}}；{{bd|1981年|8月29日}}）為美國一名[[工業設計師|工業設計師]]出身的企業家，同時也是[[Airbnb|Airbnb]]的創辦人兼[[首席執行官|首席執行官]]。2015年，《[[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]]》將切斯基名列該年度的[[時代百大人物|時代百大人物]]。<ref name=":0" />

== 早年生活與教育 ==
1981年8月29日，布萊恩·切斯基出生於[[美國|美國]][[紐約州|紐約州]]的[[尼斯卡尤納|尼斯卡尤納]]。他的雙親皆為[[社會工作|社會工作者]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fortune.com/brian-chesky-airbnb/|title=The education of Airbnb's Brian Chesky|last=Gallagher|first=Leigh|date=2015-06-26|work=Fortune|access-date=2018-03-01|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525024827/http://fortune.com/brian-chesky-airbnb/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ruthbaderginsforward">{{cite news|last1=Cohen|first1=Anne|title=Ruth Bader Ginsburg, Amy Schumer and Bibi Make Time 100 List|url=http://forward.com/the-assimilator/218726/ruth-bader-ginsburg-amy-schumer-and-bibi-make-time/|accessdate=2016-03-08|work=Forward|date=2015-04-16|archive-date=2016-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410063357/http://forward.com/the-assimilator/218726/ruth-bader-ginsburg-amy-schumer-and-bibi-make-time/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，父親羅伯特·哈利·切斯基（Robert Harry Chesky）具有[[波蘭裔美國人|波蘭裔]]和烏克蘭猶太裔血統，母親黛博拉·切斯基（Deborah Chesky）則有[[義大利裔美國人|義大利裔]]血統。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/timesunion-albany/obituary.aspx?n=harry-a-chesky&pid=118353397&fhid=5076|title=Harry Chesky Obituary|website=Albany Times Union|date=2008-10-04|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2020-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029122742/https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/timesunion-albany/obituary.aspx?n=harry-a-chesky&pid=118353397&fhid=5076}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SqT0CwAAQBAJ&pg=PT21&lpg=PT21&dq=Brian+Chesky+polish#q=Brian%20Chesky%20polish|title=The Upstarts: How Uber, Airbnb and the Killer Companies of the New Silicon Valley are Changing the World|last=Stone|first=Brad|date=2017-02-02|publisher=Transworld|isbn=9781473527027|language=en|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2020-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105095349/https://books.google.com/books?id=SqT0CwAAQBAJ&pg=PT21&lpg=PT21&dq=Brian+Chesky+polish#q=Brian%20Chesky%20polish|dead-url=no}}</ref>他在家中兩名子女中排行老大，下有一名妹妹艾莉森·切斯基（Allison Chesky）。<ref name=FortuneEducation>{{cite web |url=http://fortune.com/brian-chesky-airbnb/ |title=The education of Airbnb’s Brian Chesky |publisher=[[財富_(雜誌)|財富雜誌]] |author=Gallagher, Leigh |date=2015-07-01 |accessdate=2016-10-10 |archive-date=2019-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525024827/http://fortune.com/brian-chesky-airbnb/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>童年時期的切斯基對便藝術表現出高度興趣，除喜歡模仿他人的畫作，也愛設計新鞋和新玩具，以及將舊的鞋和玩具重新設計。<ref name=FortuneEducation />年紀稍長後，他的興趣轉向設計和[[景觀設計|景觀建築]]。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/12/business/brian-chesky-of-airbnb-on-scratching-the-itch-to-create.html|title=Brian Chesky of Airbnb, on Scratching the Itch to Create|last=Bryant|first=Adam|date=2014-10-11|work=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|access-date=2018-03-01|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223125106/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/12/business/brian-chesky-of-airbnb-on-scratching-the-itch-to-create.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

切斯基於1999年正式進入[[羅德島設計學院|羅德島設計學院]]就讀<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/brian-chesky-airbnb-ceo-life-story-photos-2017-7|title=The fabulous life of Airbnb's Brian Chesky, one of the youngest and richest tech founders in America|last=Hartmans|first=Avery|date=2017-07-22|work=Business Insider|access-date=2018-03-01|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030202425/https://www.businessinsider.com/brian-chesky-airbnb-ceo-life-story-photos-2017-7|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並於2004年獲得了[[工業設計|工業設計]]的[[美術學士|美術學士]]。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/brianchesky/|title=Brian Chesky {{!}} LinkedIn|last=|first=|date=2020-02-18|website=LinkedIn|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527092722/http://www.linkedin.com/in/brianchesky|archive-date=2010-05-27|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>於羅德島設計學院就學期間，他認識了[[喬·傑比亞|喬·傑比亞]]（Joe Gebbia），兩人之後共同創立了[[Airbnb|Airbnb]]。<ref name=nytimes/>

== 生涯 ==
自羅德島設計學院畢業後，布萊恩·切斯基來到[[洛杉磯|洛杉磯]]的3DID公司（3DID Inc.）擔任工業設計師和策劃師的工作。<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/12/business/brian-chesky-of-airbnb-on-scratching-the-itch-to-create.html?_r=2 | title=Brian Chesky of Airbnb, on Scratching the Itch to Create | newspaper=紐約時報 | date=2014-10-11 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Bryant, Adam | archive-date=2020-10-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026150935/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/12/business/brian-chesky-of-airbnb-on-scratching-the-itch-to-create.html?_r=2 | dead-url=no }}</ref>2007年，他搬到[[舊金山|舊金山]]，並和大學時期的同學[[喬·傑比亞|喬·傑比亞]]同居，共享同一個公寓單位。<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-12-03|title=FOG Design+Art Announces Galleries Participating in Seventh Edition of Fair|url=https://www.artsy.net/article/fog-design-art-fog-design-art-announces-galleries-participating-seventh-edition-fair|access-date=2020-06-24|website=Artsy|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026114718/https://www.artsy.net/article/fog-design-art-fog-design-art-announces-galleries-participating-seventh-edition-fair|dead-url=no}}</ref>同年十月，[[美國工業設計師協會|美國工業設計師協會]]於舊金山舉辦一場研討會，會場附近的酒店皆以客滿。<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://www.fastcompany.com/3027107/punk-meet-rock-airbnb-brian-chesky-chip-conley | title=Inside Airbnb's Grand Hotel Plans | magazine=Fast Company | date=2014-03-17 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Carr, Austin | archive-date=2021-01-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126130430/https://www.fastcompany.com/3027107/punk-meet-rock-airbnb-brian-chesky-chip-conley | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomiogeron/2013/01/23/airbnb-and-the-unstoppable-rise-of-the-share-economy/2/ | title=Airbnb And The Unstoppable Rise Of The Share Economy | magazine=福布斯 | date=2013-02-11 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Geron, Tomio | archive-date=2018-11-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116105216/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomiogeron/2013/01/23/airbnb-and-the-unstoppable-rise-of-the-share-economy/2/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>當時兩人正好缺錢支付該月的租金，因此決定將公寓單位出租籌款。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/21/opinion/sunday/friedman-welcome-to-the-sharing-economy.html | title=Welcome to the 'Sharing Economy' | newspaper=紐約時報 | date=2013-07-20 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Friedman, Thomas L. | archive-date=2021-03-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210306082830/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/21/opinion/sunday/friedman-welcome-to-the-sharing-economy.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>為此，他們購買了三張充氣床墊，並以「氣墊床與早餐」（Airbed and Breakfast）為概念行銷該住所，住所開放入住的第一晚便有三名旅客前來。「氣墊床與早餐」（Airbed and Breakfast）便是Airbnb公司名稱的由來。<ref>{{cite web|last=Brown Ekiel|first=Erika|title=The Entrepreneur QuestionnaireL Brian Chesky, Co-Founderv and CEO of Airbnb|url=http://greylockvc.com/post/47569079798/the-entrepreneur-questionnaire-brian-chesky|accessdate=2013-10-17|dead-url=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017222307/http://greylockvc.com/post/47569079798/the-entrepreneur-questionnaire-brian-chesky|archivedate=2013-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/201412/burt-helm/airbnb-company-of-the-year-2014.html | title=Airbnb Is Inc.'s 2014 Company of the Year | magazine=Inc. | date=2014-12 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Helm, Burt | archive-date=2021-03-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309113404/http://www.inc.com/magazine/201412/burt-helm/airbnb-company-of-the-year-2014.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2008年2月，自哈佛大學畢業的資訊工程師[[內森·布雷查兹克|內森·布雷查兹克]]（Nathan Blecharczyk）加入兩人的團隊，成為Airbnb的第三位創辦人。<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Young Tech Entrepreneurs|url=http://images.businessweek.com/ss/09/04/0421_best_young_entrepreneurs/9.htm|publisher=Bloomberg Business Week|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2014-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221134604/http://images.businessweek.com/ss/09/04/0421_best_young_entrepreneurs/9.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>三人在新成立的公司內有各自的分工，由切斯基領軍並擔任首席執行官。<ref name=FortuneEducation />為了籌備資金，由於正值[[2008年美國總統選舉|2008年美國總統選舉]]競選期間，三人根據[[貝拉克·奧巴馬|貝拉克·奧巴馬]]和[[約翰·麥凱恩|約翰·麥凱恩]]兩位候選人設計了兩款限定款麥片，分別為「奧巴馬的『O』」（Obama O’s）和「麥凱恩上校」（Cap'n McCains）。<ref>{{cite web|title=Brian Chesky: Handcrafted|url=https://mastersofscale.com/brian-chesky-handcrafted/|publisher=Masters of Scale|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2018-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522183339/https://mastersofscale.com/brian-chesky-handcrafted/|dead-url=no}}</ref>由於麥片策略大獲成功，[[Y_Combinator_(公司)|Y Combinator]]決定為[[Airbnb|Airbnb]]成立種子基金專案。<ref>{{cite web|last=Fairweather|first=Alistair|title=Brian Chesky: The homeless entrepreneur|url=http://mg.co.za/article/2013-03-12-brian-chesky-the-homeless-entrepreneur|newspaper=Mail & Guardian|accessdate=2013-10-21|archive-date=2016-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927132316/http://mg.co.za/article/2013-03-12-brian-chesky-the-homeless-entrepreneur|dead-url=no}}</ref>第一年，Airbnb開始拓展國際業務，並在歐洲成立了多處辦公室。<ref>{{cite web|last=Bradshaw|first=Tim|title=Airbnb Moves "Aggressively" into Europe|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/9051978c-8baf-11e0-a725-00144feab49a.html#axzz2hwmwfkej|accessdate=2013-10-17|archive-date=2016-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831055241/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/9051978c-8baf-11e0-a725-00144feab49a.html#axzz2hwmwfkej|dead-url=no}}</ref>2011年，切斯基為Airbnb處理客戶投訴住家遭承租人破壞一事發表公開信，他於信中宣布公司將成立24小時服務熱線，除將增加人手負責這類案件，若承租人在入住期間對房屋造成破壞或有偷竊行為而造成出租人的損失，Airbnb將提供出租人最高50,000美元的賠償金。<ref name=gawker>{{cite web|url=http://gawker.com/5827043/sleazy-airbnb-is-very-sorry-for-wrecking-your-apartment |title=Sleazy Airbnb Is 'Very Sorry' For Wrecking Your Apartment |publisher=Gawker Magazine |accessdate=2014-07-18 |dead-url=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725200133/http://gawker.com/5827043/sleazy-airbnb-is-very-sorry-for-wrecking-your-apartment |archivedate=2014-07-25}}</ref>2015年，切斯基宣布Airbnb成為在[[巴西|巴西]][[里約熱內盧|里約熱內盧]]舉行的[[2016年夏季奧林匹克運動會|2016年夏季奧林匹克運動會]]的贊助商之一，他還指出[[2014年國際足總世界盃|2014年世界杯足球賽]]期間，有超過12萬名旅客入住Airbnb的住所。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/airbnb-ceo-brian-chesky-global-expansion-cuba-legal-pushback/ | title=Airbnb CEO on global expansion and legal pushback | publisher=CBS News | date=2015-04-22 | accessdate=2016-03-08 | author=Kashdan, Jason | archive-date=2021-01-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104083723/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/airbnb-ceo-brian-chesky-global-expansion-cuba-legal-pushback/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>截止2015年3月，Airbnb的估值為200億美元。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jason |first1=Klampet |title=Airbnb's New $1 Billion Funding Would Value It At $20 Billion |url=http://skift.com/2015/02/28/airbnbs-new-1-billion-funding-would-value-it-at-20-billion/ |website=skift.com |publisher=Skift |accessdate=2015-03-26 |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402145410/http://skift.com/2015/02/28/airbnbs-new-1-billion-funding-would-value-it-at-20-billion/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2017年4月，切斯基受邀參加[[領英|領英]]創辦人[[里德·霍夫曼|里德·霍夫曼]]所主持的[[播客|播客]]節目《[[擴張大師|擴張大師]]》（{{lang-en|Masters of Scale}}），同為第一批受訪者的還有[[馬克·扎克伯格|馬克·扎克伯格]]、[[約翰·埃爾坎|約翰·埃爾坎]]和[[戴安·格林|戴安·格林]]。他在節目中討論Airbnb如何在不同尺度上實現擴張，他認為許多本身無法擴張的小細節往往才是企業得以擴張的關鍵。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mastersofscale.com/brian-chesky-handcrafted/|title=Master of scale - Brian Chesky|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2018-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522183339/https://mastersofscale.com/brian-chesky-handcrafted/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

切斯基和美國前總統[[貝拉克·奧巴馬|貝拉克·奧巴馬]]私交甚深，兩人有定期通話的習慣。切斯基於[[卡拉·斯維什爾|卡拉·斯維什爾]]主持的播客節目上指出，[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情|2019冠狀病毒病疫情]]爆發後，奧巴馬在美國媒體普遍還未關注疫情的時候便已在電話中提醒他，Airbnb要為疫情擴散做好萬全準備。<ref>{{cite web|title=Brian Chesky: These 9 weeks were the most stressful in Airbnb's history|url=https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/brian-chesky-these-9-weeks-were-most-stressful-in-airbnbs/id1011668648?i=1000475440439|publisher=Recode By Vox|access-date=2020-10-22|archive-date=2021-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201221034/https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/brian-chesky-these-9-weeks-were-most-stressful-in-airbnbs/id1011668648?i=1000475440439|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 慈善事業 ==
2016年6月1日，布萊恩·切斯基加入[[捐贈誓言|捐贈誓言]]計畫，該計畫由一群身價超過10億美元的富豪所發起，他們承諾將自己多數的財產捐出，成員包括[[沃倫·巴菲特|沃倫·巴菲特]]和[[比爾·蓋茨|比爾·蓋茨]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fortune.com/2016/06/01/airbnb-cofounders-join-buffett-and-gates-giving-pledge/ |title=Airbnb Cofounders Join Buffett and Gates' 'Giving Pledge' |publisher=[[財富_(雜誌)|財富雜誌]] |date=2016-06-01 |accessdate=2016-10-10 |archive-date=2017-02-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170217134846/http://fortune.com/2016/06/01/airbnb-cofounders-join-buffett-and-gates-giving-pledge/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>切斯基如此形容自己加入捐贈誓言的動機：「我加入這項計畫便是希望幫助更多孩子能像我一樣實現自己的夢想，走過和我相似的人生歷程。我要讓他們知道，他們的夢想不應被他們眼前能看到的事物所限制，他們的可能性沒有極限。華特·迪士尼曾說過：『只要你夢想得到的事情，你一定能將之實現。』我希望引導這些孩子實現夢想。」<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://givingpledge.org/Pledger.aspx?id=180|title=Brian Chesky - The Giving Pledge|website=givingpledge.org|access-date=2017-12-16|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115154052/https://givingpledge.org/Pledger.aspx?id=180|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 殊榮 ==
2015年，布萊恩·切斯基除了名列當年《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》雜誌所發布的美國40歲以下富豪榜名單中<ref>{{cite magazine | url=https://www.forbes.com/40under40/ | title=40 Under 40 | magazine=福布斯 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | archive-date=2016-12-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161207031552/http://www.forbes.com/40under40/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>，還成為《[[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]]》該年度的[[時代百大人物|時代百大人物]]之一。<ref name=":0">{{cite magazine | url=http://time.com/3822568/brian-chesky-2015-time-100/ | title=TIME 100 Pioneers: Brian Chesky | magazine=時代雜誌 | date=2015-04-16 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Ive, Jonathan | archive-date=2021-01-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120233724/https://time.com/3822568/brian-chesky-2015-time-100/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>同年5月，時任美國總統[[貝拉克·奧巴馬|貝拉克·奧巴馬]]任命切斯基為[[全球創業精神總統大使|全球創業精神總統大使]]之一。<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2015/05/11/airbnb-kind-snacks-white-house-celebrates-entrepreneurs-around-world | title=The White House Celebrates Entrepreneurs Around the World | publisher=The White House Blog | date=2015-05-11 | accessdate=2016-02-23 | author=Brayton, Jenna | archive-date=2016-10-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022153457/https://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2015/05/11/airbnb-kind-snacks-white-house-celebrates-entrepreneurs-around-world | dead-url=no }}</ref>切斯基還是2016年[[福布斯美國400富豪榜|福布斯美國400富豪榜]]中最年輕的富豪。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/gfgl45gekf/brian-chesky/#3c74d93f42a3|title=Brian Chesky - pg.9|last=Vinton|first=Kate|website=福布斯|access-date=2017-05-23|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030041636/https://www.forbes.com/pictures/gfgl45gekf/brian-chesky/#3c74d93f42a3|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年，舊金山商業時報將該年度[[舊金山灣區|灣區]]最佳執行長這一稱號頒給了切斯基。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2018/12/18/2018-bay-area-executive-of-the-year-airbnb-chesky.html|title=Brian Chesky grew Airbnb from three airbeds in a living room to the biggest force in hospitality. He's the 2018 Executive of the Year (Video)|website=www.bizjournals.com|access-date=2019-03-06|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021141637/https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2018/12/18/2018-bay-area-executive-of-the-year-airbnb-chesky.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

